title: Banca di Roma - Wikipedia
snippet: In 2002, Banca di Roma Group merged with Bipop Carire to form Capitalia. In 2007 Capitalia was acquired by UniCredit, which Banca di Roma became its subsidiary instead. In 2008, 11 branches were sold to Banca Carige.

title: FRB: Press Release -- Approval of proposal of Banca di Roma -- August 13, 2002
snippet: For immediate release · The Federal Reserve Board announced today the approval of the application of Banca di Roma, S.p.A., Rome, Italy, to establish branches in New York, New York, and Chicago, Illinois, and an agency in San Francisco, California

title: IBL Banca becomes Official Banking Partner of AS Roma
snippet: IBL Banca has become the Official Banking Partner of AS Roma, the most recent Centurion partner to join the Giallorossi family.
